  "poem": {
    "content": "The old vendor, still as stone,\nkept a record in his bone.\nOf thunder, a Latin curse,\nechoing through the universe.\n\nHe watched the oven slowly rise,\na helmet of heat across the skies.\nThe term was up, the debt unpaid,\nhis weary soul, a game betrayed.\n\nThey came to destroy all he possessed,\nhe saw their shadows, darkly dressed.\nA metal frame within the door,\nsqueezing tight against the floor.\n\nHe wanted to quit, to run away,\nbut concrete held him fast that day.\nHe raised a hand, a futile plea,\nhis skin, a map of misery.\n\nA broken leg, a silent scream,\nhis shattered vision, a fever dream.\nThe still, small voice within his head,\nwhispered of ashes, softly spread.",
